race.comment: REUBEN HILL (2) stuck on well last time to finish 1.75 lengths back in third (28.52) at Bendigo in a Grade 4/5 over 500m. One of the leading chances. BLACK STATESMAN (1) doesn't have the best strike-rate. Finished in the money last time though when second (25.96) at this track. Form at the trip sound including four wins. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. Can measure up. PRISON BREAK (7) goes very well this trip starting eight times for four wins and two minors. In the money last time at this track (22.56) in a Grade 4/5, finishing a 4.5 lengths second. Can feature with the right run. ASTON RYAN (5) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.
